        "decision": "Reports generated as CSV and PDF",
        "implementation_note": "MJ's assumption — Bird never specified formats. Implement CSV first (simpler, testable). PDF can follow. Use a strategy pattern (IReportFormatter) so adding formats later is trivial."
      },
      {
        "decision": "GET /reports?format=csv|pdf&start_date=&end_date=",
        "implementation_note": "MJ's API design. Reasonable RESTful default. Consider: should this be GET (synchronous) or POST (async job creation) given Pippen's performance concern? Recommend: implement both — GET for small ranges, POST /reports/jobs for large ranges returning a job ID."
      },
      {
        "decision": "Consider async generation with job ID for large date ranges",
        "implementation_note": "Pippen's recommendation. No SLA defined for report generation time. Shaq should implement a size/range threshold that triggers async path. Suggest: ranges > 90 days go async. Return 202 Accepted with a job ID and a GET /reports/jobs/{id} polling endpoint."
      }
